	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=1999&mid=1007124325990>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=1999&mid=1007124325990>RE: Good Spare?</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=1999&mid=1007124325990#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Nov 30th 7:45 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=102727><span id= >AMPMagic</span></a><br><span id=notbold>11 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><br>This is how it works.<br><br>Magic Resistance is used to resist magic (all harmful magic, and has been know to block area affect spells cast by allies that should hurt you)<br>Now lets say you are like me 50 MR and 94 CR that means when a mob casts a cold based spell I will have a chance to resist it, If I dont and it hits me I will reduce the effect. I love fighting wizzies that use alot of cold based spells in combat, be them in duel every time!<br>MR also reduces duration of a spell effect. <br>So MR is important to have, and its best to get the other resists (focus in the one your class/race faces alot)<br>I know many pallies prefer DR cuase of the heavy contact from undead. I as a Ranger find myself getting hit with every Ice spell in the book. (side note with 94 CR the most powerful ice spell I have been hit with hits for 15dmg hehe)(hits my buddies alot more harder)<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
