	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Apr 8th 6:16 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=117647><span id= >Amneth</span></a><br><span id=notbold>42 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hrmm.<br><br>This is pretty much incorrect. MR is figured seperately from fr/cr/pr/dr. It is not additive. When you get into a fight with a caster though, its always good to have your mr up as high as possible given that alot of the general spells are resisted off of MR. however the only time a spell will use two resists of this sort is a spell that has multiple effects. So for instance, most nukes are off of just one resist. <br><br>Even in these cases (somewhat rare) each resist is rolled seperately, the two numbers are not added together.<br><br>AFAIK<br><br>-Amneth</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
